<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1436,806,1312]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[151,280,806,831]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Zero to five, commonly three, pairs of branchiae; when present, they begin on segment 2; lateral lappets present or absent; ventral shields from segment 2; nephridial papillae on segments 2–5; 40 or less pairs of notopodia from segment 2; chaetae smooth-tipped, limbate; pairs of neuropodia from segment 5; uncini avicular with button-shaped subrostral process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1436,806,1312]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[198,310,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Holthe, T." box="[489,675,966,992]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 236" refId="ref62170" refString="Holthe, T. (1986 b) Evolution, Systematics, and Distribution of the Polychaeta Terebellomorpha, with a catalogue of the taxa and a bibliography. Gunneria, 55, 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="1986">Holthe (1986b)</bibRefCitation>
, only two species described are valid for the Grand 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1316,1436,966,992]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="73" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
region: 
<taxonomicName authority="Kritzler, 1971" authorityName=", Kritzler" authorityYear="1971" box="[244,707,1006,1032]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hartmanae">
<emphasis box="[244,527,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Streblosoma hartmanae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kritzler, H." box="[538,707,1006,1032]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="904 - 913" refId="ref62762" refString="Kritzler, H. (1971) Observation on a new species of Streblosoma from the Northeast Gulf of Mexico (Polychaeta: Terebellidae). Bulletin of Marine Science, 21 (4), 904 - 913." type="journal article" year="1971">Kritzler, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from Florida, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrill, 1900" authorityName=", Verrill" authorityYear="1900" box="[947,1301,1006,1032]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="polybranchia">
<emphasis box="[947,1136,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">S. polybranchia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill, A. E." box="[1147,1301,1006,1032]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="595 - 671" refId="ref64919" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1900) Additions to the Turbellaria, Nemertina, and Annelida of the Bermudas, with a revision of the New England genera and species. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, 10, 595 - 671." type="journal article" year="1900">Verrill, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry name="Bermuda" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." box="[232,415,1046,1072]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="243 - 310" refId="ref61792" refString="Hartman, O. (1956) Polychaetous annelids erected by Treadwell, 1891 - 1948, together with a brief chronology. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 109 (2), 243 - 310." type="journal article" year="1956">Hartman (1956</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." box="[429,489,1046,1072]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="355 - 628" refId="ref61833" refString="Hartman, O. (1959) Catalogue of the Polychaetous Annelids of the World. Part 2. Allan Hancock Foundations Publications, Occasional Papers, 23 (2), 355 - 628." type="journal article" year="1959">1959</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Holthe, T." box="[558,739,1046,1072]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 236" refId="ref62170" refString="Holthe, T. (1986 b) Evolution, Systematics, and Distribution of the Polychaeta Terebellomorpha, with a catalogue of the taxa and a bibliography. Gunneria, 55, 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="1986">Holthe (1986b)</bibRefCitation>
noticed that 
<taxonomicName authority="Treadwell, 1911" authorityName="Treadwell" authorityYear="1911" box="[897,1213,1046,1072]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verrilli">
<emphasis box="[897,1009,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">S. verrilli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Treadwell, A. L." box="[1019,1213,1046,1072]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref64673" refString="Treadwell, A. L. (1911) Polychaetous annelids from the Dry Tortugas, Florida. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 30, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1911">Treadwell, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from Florida, is a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[386,595,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Quatrefages" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[386,591,1086,1111]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Thelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="setosus">Thelepus setosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Nevertheless, based upon the 
<typeStatus box="[970,1020,1086,1112]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
specimen, this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leuckart" authorityYear="1849" box="[151,257,1126,1151]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Thelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,257,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Thelepus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being redescribed as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Treadwell, 1911)" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[516,925,1126,1152]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Thelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verrilli" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[516,710,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Thelepus verrilli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Treadwell, A. L." box="[725,918,1126,1152]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref64673" refString="Treadwell, A. L. (1911) Polychaetous annelids from the Dry Tortugas, Florida. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 30, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1911">Treadwell, 1911</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[932,1064,1126,1152]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, (see below). A third species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Streblosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tenhovei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">S. tenhovei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[257,350,1166,1192]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is also described.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1436,806,1312]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
The original generic description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars, M." box="[620,756,1206,1232]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="406 - 417" refId="ref64346" refString="Sars, M. (1872) Diagnoser af nye annelider fra Christiania-fjorden. Forhandlinger fra Videnskabs-Selskabet i Christiania, 1871, 406 - 417. (Issued by G. O. Sars)." type="journal article" year="1872">Sars (1872)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the genus may or may not have eyespots, and that uncini were uniserial (MF:1). However, uncini may have more than one tooth present above the main fang.
</paragraph>
